sect2.title: SWR_ICAS1_Diag_115
sect2.para:
Requirement is satisfied here: Rte_Read_OperationCycleMenagement_Motor54_bl_DrivingCycle ../../../../../../../../sw.sys.chorus_main_build/mc_sw/cdd/UDS_Services_Chorus/OperationCycleMenagement/c/src/OperationCycleMenagement.c line 534
Requirement is not verified The ICAS1 shall enable/disable the evaluation of the preconditions for all diagnostic requests depending on the State "OBD Driving Cycle" as follows:
- If this state is OBD_Driving_Cycle_notSet then ICAS1 shall disable the evaluation of the preconditions. This means that all diagnostic service requests will be accepted in terms of "preconditions"
- If this state is OBD_Driving_Cycle_setOnce then ICAS1 shall check the defined preconditions, when ICAS1 receives a diagnostic request for a service which needs the evaluation of preconditions. If at least one of the checks fails, then ICAS1 shall respond with NRC 0x22.
- If this state is OBD_Driving_Cycle_setOnce then ICAS1 shall check the defined preconditions also while the function started by the service is active (refer to column "Applicable during active diagnostic service" in SWR_ICAS1_Diag_114). As soon as at least one precondition is getting false, ICAS1 shall return to the default function. a) This applies to service 0x28: When the preconditions are no more fulfilled, mute mode shall be aborted as described in SWR_ICAS1_Diag_211. b) This applies to service 0x85: When the preconditions are no more fulfilled, DTC setting shall be reenabled. This is not described in SWR_ICAS1_Diag_341 !
The state "OBD Driving Cycle" is determined according to the state chart in SWR_ICAS1_Diag_121. ID: SWR_ICAS1_Diag_115 _ObjectType: Requirement ASIL: QM
